# Feature Specification: Feature Update and Delete (CRUD Completion)

**Feature Branch**: `crud-feature`

**Created**: 2026-06-26

**Status**: Draft

**Input**: User description: "Add Update and Delete operations to features so the full CRUD lifecycle is supported in the Dev Team UI and API. Features can be renamed, reprioritized, and removed when no longer needed."

## Workspace Summary (Brownfield)

The Dev Team platform is an existing Go backend (`cmd/devteam`, `internal/api`, `internal/feature`, `internal/db`) with a React/TypeScript frontend (`ui/`). This feature extends the existing feature resource with the missing Update (U) and Delete (D) operations.

**Existing API surface** (discovered in `internal/api/server.go`):
- `GET /api/features` ‚Äî list (exists)
- `POST /api/features` ‚Äî create (exists)
- `GET /api/features/{id}` ‚Äî read single (exists)
- `POST /api/features/{id}/cancel` ‚Äî cancel (exists)
- `POST /api/features/{id}/recirculate` ‚Äî recirculate (exists)
=== acceptance ===
# Acceptance Criteria: Feature Update and Delete (CRUD Completion)

**Spec**: crud-feature
**Created**: 2026-06-26

## US-1: Rename and Reprioritize a Feature

- **AC-001**: Given a feature with `status: draft`, when a client sends `PATCH /api/features/{id}` with `{"title":"Renamed","priority":2}`, then the response is `200` with JSON body where `title=="Renamed"`, `priority==2`, `id` unchanged, and `updated_at > previous updated_at`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: `httptest` request to PATCH handler; assert status 200, decode JSON, compare fields.
- **AC-002**: Given a feature with `status: in_progress`, when a client sends `PATCH /api/features/{id}` with valid body, then the response is `409 Conflict` with JSON body `{"error":"..."}` containing a message about the busy state.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: `httptest`; assert 409, decode `error` field non-empty.
- **AC-003**: Given a feature with `status: waiting_for_feedback`, when a client sends `PATCH /api/features/{id}`, then the response is `409 Conflict`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: `httptest`; assert 409.
- **AC-004**: Given no feature with id `missing-id`, when a client sends `PATCH /api/features/missing-id`, then the response is `404 Not Found` with a JSON error body.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: `httptest`; assert 404, decode `error` field.
- **AC-005**: Given a draft feature, when a client sends `PATCH` with `{"title":"","priority":1}`, then the response is `400 Bad Request`.
=== repos ===
repos:
  - name: devteam
    path: .
    role: primary
    changes: |
      Add PATCH /api/features/{id} (update title+priority) and DELETE /api/features/{id} (hard delete with cascade).
      Wire to existing UpdateFeature/DeleteFeature data-layer functions. Add 409 guards for non-{draft,done,cancelled} states.
      Broadcast feature_updated / feature_deleted SSE events. Add UI edit form and delete-with-confirm on the feature detail page.
      Gate affordances by status. Go handlers + httptest integration tests; Playwright E2E for UI flows.
