## US-001: Rename / reprioritize a feature

AC-001: Given a draft feature with id "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"title":"New Title","priority":1}`, then the response is 200 with a FeatureDetailResponse whose `title`=="New Title", `priority`==1, `id`=="f1" (unchanged), and `updated_at` is later than the previously stored value.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH, assert 200, assert response body fields, then GET /api/features/f1 and assert the persisted values match.

AC-002: Given a draft feature "f1" exists with title "Old", when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"title":"New"}` (priority omitted), then the response is 200 and the priority is unchanged from its prior value (partial edit ‚Äî only provided fields update).
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with only title, assert 200, assert priority equals the pre-edit value.

AC-003: Given a draft feature "f1" exists with priority 2, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"priority":3}` (title omitted), then the response is 200 and the title is unchanged.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with only priority, assert 200, assert title equals the pre-edit value.

AC-004: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "done", when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with a valid body, then the response is 200 and the edit succeeds (terminal-but-not-in-progress features are editable).
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Set feature status to "done", send PATCH, assert 200 and updated fields.

AC-005: Given no feature with id "missing" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/missing is sent, then the response is 404 with body `{"error":"feature_not_found","details":"..."}`.
  Test level: smoke
  Verification: Send PATCH to a non-existent id, assert 404 and the error code string.

AC-006: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "in_progress", when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with a valid body, then the response is 409 with body `{"error":"feature_in_progress","details":"..."}` and the feature's title and priority are unchanged on subsequent GET.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Set feature status to "in_progress", send PATCH, assert 409, then GET and assert unchanged fields.

AC-007: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "waiting_for_feedback", when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with a valid body, then the response is 409 `feature_in_progress` and the feature is unchanged.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Same as AC-006 with status "waiting_for_feedback".

AC-008: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"title":"   "}` (whitespace-only), then the response is 400 with error code `empty_title`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with whitespace title, assert 400 and error code.

AC-009: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"title":"` + "a"*201 + `"}`, then the response is 400 with error code `title_too_long`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with 201-char title, assert 400 and error code.

AC-010: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"priority":4}`, then the response is 400 with error code `invalid_priority`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with priority 4, assert 400 and error code.

AC-011: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"priority":0}`, then the response is 400 with error code `invalid_priority` (0 is not a valid value on edit, unlike create where 0 means "default").
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with priority 0, assert 400 and error code.

AC-012: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with body `{"id":"different","title":"X"}`, then the response is 400 with error code `validation_error` and details mentioning id is immutable, and the feature's id remains "f1".
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with an id field, assert 400, assert error code, then GET and assert id unchanged.

AC-013: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with a malformed JSON body, then the response is 400 with error code `validation_error`.
  Test level: smoke
  Verification: Send PATCH with body `{not json`, assert 400 and error code.

AC-014: Given a feature "f1" exists, when a PATCH /api/features/f1 is sent with a body larger than 1 MiB, then the request is rejected (MaxBytesReader) and the connection is terminated.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Send PATCH with a 2 MiB body, assert the request fails (not 200).

AC-015: Given a draft feature "f1" exists, when a user opens the feature detail page in the browser and clicks the edit affordance, then an edit form appears with title and priority fields pre-filled with the current values.
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî navigate to /features/f1, click edit, assert the form is visible and the input values match the feature's current title and priority.

AC-016: Given the edit form is open on the feature detail page, when the user changes the title and priority and clicks save, then the form closes, the detail page shows the new title and priority, and a subsequent reload shows the persisted values.
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî fill the edit form, click save, assert the detail page reflects new values, reload, assert values persist.

AC-017: Given a feature "f1" has status "in_progress", when the user opens the feature detail page, then the edit affordance is not visible (or is disabled).
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî set feature to in_progress (or observe an in_progress feature), open detail page, assert the edit control is absent/disabled.

---

## US-002: Delete a feature

AC-018: Given a draft feature "f1" exists with related questions/notes rows, when a DELETE /api/features/f1 is sent, then the response is 204 with no body, and a subsequent GET /api/features/f1 returns 404 `feature_not_found`, and GET /api/features no longer includes "f1".
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Insert feature + related rows, send DELETE, assert 204, assert GET returns 404, assert list excludes f1.

AC-019: Given a draft feature "f1" exists with rows in questions, notes, gate_history, sessions, recirculations, events, and spec_artifacts referencing f1, when a DELETE /api/features/f1 is sent, then all those rows are removed (cascade-delete verified by direct DB query returning zero rows for each table where feature_id/id = 'f1').
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Insert rows in every related table, send DELETE, query each table, assert 0 rows.

AC-020: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "done", when a DELETE /api/features/f1 is sent, then the response is 204 (terminal features are deletable).
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Set feature status to "done", send DELETE, assert 204.

AC-021: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "cancelled", when a DELETE /api/features/f1 is sent, then the response is 204.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Set feature status to "cancelled", send DELETE, assert 204.

AC-022: Given no feature "missing" exists, when a DELETE /api/features/missing is sent, then the response is 404 with error code `feature_not_found`.
  Test level: smoke
  Verification: Send DELETE to non-existent id, assert 404 and error code.

AC-023: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "in_progress", when a DELETE /api/features/f1 is sent, then the response is 409 with error code `feature_in_progress` and the feature is unchanged on subsequent GET.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Set feature to in_progress, send DELETE, assert 409, then GET and assert the feature still exists with original fields.

AC-024: Given a feature "f1" exists with status "waiting_for_feedback", when a DELETE /api/features/f1 is sent, then the response is 409 `feature_in_progress` and the feature is unchanged.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Same as AC-023 with status "waiting_for_feedback".

AC-025: Given a draft feature "f1" exists, when a user opens the feature detail page and clicks the delete button, then a confirm dialog appears.
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî navigate to /features/f1, click delete, assert a confirmation dialog/modal is visible.

AC-026: Given the delete confirm dialog is open, when the user confirms, then the DELETE request is sent, the response is 204, and the browser navigates to the dashboard, and "f1" no longer appears in the feature list.
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî click delete, confirm, assert URL is the dashboard, assert the feature card for f1 is absent.

AC-027: Given the delete confirm dialog is open, when the user cancels the dialog, then no DELETE request is sent and the feature remains.
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî click delete, cancel, assert no network DELETE request, assert feature still listed.

AC-028: Given a feature "f1" has status "in_progress", when the user opens the feature detail page, then the delete button is not visible (or is disabled).
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright ‚Äî open an in_progress feature's detail page, assert delete button is absent/disabled.

---

## US-003: Block edits while processing

AC-029: Given a feature "f1" with status "in_progress", when the Feature.Edit method is called, then it returns an error and the feature's title and priority are not modified.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Construct a Feature with status in_progress, call Edit, assert error is non-nil, assert fields unchanged.

AC-030: Given a feature "f1" with status "waiting_for_feedback", when the Feature.Edit method is called, then it returns an error and the feature is unchanged.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Same as AC-029 with status waiting_for_feedback.

AC-031: Given a feature "f1" with status "draft", when the Feature.Edit method is called with valid title "X" and priority 2, then it returns nil and the feature's title=="X", priority==2, and UpdatedAt is refreshed.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Construct a draft Feature, call Edit, assert nil error, assert fields and UpdatedAt.

AC-032: Given a feature "f1" with status "done", when the Feature.Edit method is called with valid inputs, then it returns nil and the edit succeeds.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Construct a done Feature, call Edit, assert nil error, assert fields updated.

---

## US-004: Block delete of in-progress features

AC-033: Given a feature "f1" with status "in_progress", the DELETE endpoint returns 409 before any DB deletion occurs, and the feature row and all its related rows remain intact.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Insert feature + related rows, set status in_progress, send DELETE, assert 409, query DB, assert all rows still present.

AC-034: Given a feature "f1" with status "waiting_for_feedback", the DELETE endpoint returns 409 and no rows are deleted.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Same as AC-033 with status waiting_for_feedback.

