## Workspace Summary (Brownfield)

This feature is added to the **Dev Team platform itself** ‚Äî an AI-DLC orchestrator written in Go (backend) with a React/TypeScript frontend.

- **Repo**: `devteam` (self-hosted platform). Worktree: `/home/lobsterdog/worktrees/devteam-specs/crud-feature` on branch `spec/crud-feature`.
- **Backend**: Go 1.x, stdlib `net/http` with Go 1.22 `mux.HandleFunc("METHOD /path", ...)` pattern routing. SQLite (default) or PostgreSQL via `database:` config in `devteam.yaml`. Migrations versioned in `internal/db/migration_NNN.go`, registered via `RegisterMigration`, run in transaction on startup, adapted for both SQLite+Postgres.
- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript + Vite. Components in `ui/src/components/`, pages in `ui/src/pages/` (`Dashboard.tsx`, `FeatureDetail.tsx`). API client in `ui/src/api/client.ts`. E2E: Playwright (`ui/e2e/`, port 18765).
- **Existing feature model** (`internal/feature/feature.go`):
  - `Feature` struct: `ID` (immutable slug), `Title`, `Current Phase`, `Status`, `Priority` (int 1-3), `IntakePath`, `SpecDir`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`, `Dependencies`, `Repos`, `PreparedRepos`, `PhaseStates`.
  - Status enum: `draft, in_progress, gate_blocked, passed, failed, done, recirculated, cancelled, waiting_for_feedback`.
  - Phase enum: `inception, planning, construction, review, testing, delivery`.
  - Methods: `NewFeature`, `Start`, `AdvanceTo`, `RecirculateTo`, `Cancel`, `MarkDone`, `IsTerminal`, `Slug`.
  - `Priority` validated by `IsValidPriority` (1-3).
- **Existing API** (`internal/api/server.go`):
  - `GET /api/features` ‚Üí `listFeatures` (returns `{"features":[...], "total_count":N}`)
  - `POST /api/features` ‚Üí `createFeature` (validates title 1-200 chars, description non-empty, priority 1-3 defaulting 2; type `loose_idea|external_spec`)
  - `GET /api/features/{id}` ‚Üí `getFeature`
  - `POST /api/features/{id}/cancel` ‚Üí `cancelFeature`
  - `POST /api/features/{id}/recirculate` ‚Üí `recirculateFeature`
  - No PATCH/PUT/DELETE for feature metadata. No edit endpoint. No delete endpoint.
- **Existing UI**: `FeatureDetail.tsx` renders a feature; `FeatureCard.tsx`/`FeatureList.tsx` for the dashboard. Cancel/recirculate actions exist. No edit form, no delete button.
- **Conventions to follow**:
  - Error responses use `writeError(w, status, code, message)` with `{error, details}` shape (see `ErrorResponse` DTO). Codes are snake_case strings (`empty_title`, `title_too_long`, `invalid_priority`, `feature_not_found`, `internal_error`, `validation_error`).
  - Success responses use `writeJSON(w, status, payload)`.
  - Request body size capped via `http.MaxBytesReader(w, r.Body, 1<<20)` (1 MiB).
  - JSON arrays initialized to `[]` not `null` (e.g. `FeaturesToSummaryResponse` uses `make([]..., 0, len(...))`).
  - DB writes guarded by `if s.db != nil`.
  - Feature rows in `features` table; questions/notes/etc. have FK to `features.id`. Cascade-delete must remove related rows (questions, notes, gate_history, sessions, recirculations, events, spec_artifacts).
  - Phase routing uses Go 1.22 `"METHOD /path"` string pattern; `{id}` path values via `r.PathValue("id")`.
  - No constitution.md present ‚Äî no project-level principles to gate against.

