# Acceptance Criteria ‚Äî multiple-llm-providers

Every criterion follows Given/When/Then with an explicit test level and verification method. Constraint IDs (CON-*) trace to the constraint register in `spec.md`.

## US-1 ‚Äî Operator configures a provider and assigns it per role

AC-001: Given a `devteam.yaml` with a `providers:` section defining provider `p1` (`base_url: http://x`, `api_key_env: K`), and `roles.pm.provider: p1` with `roles.pm.model: m1`, when the PM agent is dispatched, then the generated `opencode.json` in the temp `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` declares provider `p1` and model `m1`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: parse the generated `opencode.json` (capture the temp dir path during dispatch) and assert it contains the `base_url` and `model` for `p1`/`m1`. Covers CON-002, CON-006, FR-003.

AC-002: Given two providers `anthropic` (`base_url: http://a`) and `local` (`base_url: http://b`), and `roles.developer.provider: local`, `roles.pm.provider: anthropic`, when a developer dispatch and a pm dispatch are each run, then the developer's generated `opencode.json` contains `http://b` and the pm's contains `http://a`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: two dispatches, two captured `opencode.json` files, assert `base_url` differs per role. Covers CON-006, FR-002.

AC-003: Given `devteam.yaml` with no `providers:` key, when any role is dispatched, then the generated `opencode.json` has no provider/model override fields and the dispatch succeeds.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: capture generated `opencode.json`, assert absence of model/provider keys; assert `DispatchResult.Success == true`. Covers CON-010, FR-006.

AC-004: Given `devteam.yaml` with `providers:` defined but role `reviewer` has no provider mapping, when the reviewer agent is dispatched, then no override is written for that role and opencode's default applies (dispatch succeeds).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: generated `opencode.json` for the reviewer dispatch has no model override; `DispatchResult.Success == true`. Covers CON-010, FR-006.

AC-005: Given `devteam.yaml` with a duplicate provider name (`providers:` lists `p1` twice), when config is loaded, then loading fails with an error containing "duplicate provider name: p1".
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config.LoadConfig` returns a non-nil error whose message matches "duplicate provider name". Covers FR-007.

AC-006: Given `devteam.yaml` where `roles.developer.provider: ghost` and `ghost` is not in `providers:`, when config is loaded, then loading fails with an error naming role `developer` and provider `ghost`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config.LoadConfig` returns error matching "role 'developer' references unknown provider 'ghost'". Covers FR-007.

AC-007: Given `devteam.yaml` where provider `p1` has an empty `base_url`, when config is loaded, then loading fails with "provider 'p1' has empty base_url".
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config.LoadConfig` returns error matching "provider 'p1' has empty base_url". Covers FR-007.

AC-008: Given a provider `p1` with no default `model` and a role mapping `roles.pm.provider: p1` with no `model`, when config is loaded, then loading fails with "role 'pm' has no model and provider 'p1' has no default model".
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config.LoadConfig` returns the matching error. Covers FR-007, Error Scenarios table.

AC-009: Given `devteam.yaml` where `providers:` is an empty map (`providers: {}`), when any role is dispatched, then no override is written and the dispatch succeeds (treated as absent, not an error).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: dispatch succeeds; `opencode.json` has no model override. Covers Empty State Behavior, FR-006.

## US-2 ‚Äî Operator supplies API credentials via environment variables

AC-010: Given provider `p1` with `api_key_env: OPENAI_API_KEY` and the process environment has `OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-test`, when an agent is dispatched against `p1`, then the agent process environment contains `OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-test` and the on-disk `devteam.yaml` contains only the literal string `OPENAI_API_KEY` (never the key value).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: inspect the dispatched process env (or the env passed to tmux/exec) and assert `OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-test`; grep `devteam.yaml` for `sk-test` and assert zero matches. Covers CON-004, FR-004.

AC-011: Given a successful dispatch of a provider-mapped role, when log output is inspected, then no API key value appears in any log line.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: run a dispatch with `K=sk-secret`, capture the session log (`logs/<phase>-<role>.log`) and stdout/stderr, assert `sk-secret` does not appear. Covers CON-004, FR-004.

AC-012: Given provider `p1` with `api_key_env: MISSING_KEY` and `MISSING_KEY` is not set in the environment, when Dev Team dispatches an agent against `p1`, then the dispatch fails fast (no opencode process is spawned) with `DispatchResult.Success == false` and `Error` containing "api key env var 'MISSING_KEY' is not set".
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert no `opencode` child process is started (mock/stub the spawner) and `DispatchResult.Error` matches the expected message. Covers CON-005, FR-005.

AC-013: Given `api_key_env: K` and `K` is set but empty (`K=""`), when a dispatch against that provider is attempted, then the dispatch fails fast as if the variable were missing.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: with `K=""` the dispatch result is `Success=false` with the missing-env error. Covers Edge Cases, FR-005.

## US-3 ‚Äî Dispatch fails fast on provider/auth errors

AC-014: Given a provider `p1` with `base_url: http://127.0.0.1:1` (port refused) and a valid `api_key_env` value, when an agent is dispatched against `p1`, then `DispatchResult.Success == false` and `DispatchResult.Error` contains a message identifying the provider failure.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: run a real dispatch (or a dispatch against a stub server returning connection refused) and assert the error string references the provider/endpoint. Covers CON-005, FR-005.

AC-015: Given a dispatch that has failed with a provider/auth error, when the dispatch completes, then no retry attempt was made and no secondary provider was selected (exactly one spawn attempt, one failure).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: count spawn calls to the opencode dispatcher (mock the spawner); assert exactly one invocation. Covers CON-005, FR-005.

AC-016: Given a provider returning HTTP 401 on first request, when an agent is dispatched, then the dispatch result captures the auth error in `Error` and `Success == false` (the error surfaces to the operator; it is not swallowed).
  Test level: integration
  Verification: point the provider `base_url` at an httptest server returning 401, dispatch, assert `Success == false` and `Error` mentions 401/auth. Covers CON-005, FR-005.

## US-4 ‚Äî Backward-compatible default when no provider is configured

AC-017: Given a `devteam.yaml` with no `providers:` section (pre-feature shape), when config is loaded and any role dispatched, then config loads without error and the generated `opencode.json` is byte-identical (in the relevant fields) to the pre-feature output.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: diff generated `opencode.json` against a baseline captured before the feature; assert no new fields added. Covers CON-010, FR-006.

AC-018: Given `devteam.yaml` has `providers:` and role mappings for some roles but not `tester`, when the tester agent is dispatched, then no override is written for tester and the dispatch succeeds.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: generated `opencode.json` for the tester dispatch has no model override; `Success == true`. Covers CON-010, FR-006.

## Cross-cutting (constraint conformance)

AC-019: Given the full implementation source, when grepped for provider-specific string comparisons (e.g. `== "anthropic"`, `== "openai"`, `case "anthropic"`), then zero matches exist outside of tests and comments.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `rg -n 'anthropic|openai|ollama' internal/` (excluding tests/comments) returns no provider-dispatch logic. Covers CON-003, FR-008, SC-005.

AC-020: Given the implementation, when the web UI source (`ui/src/`) is inspected, then no provider/model display or editing surface is added.
  Test level: smoke
  Verification: `rg -n 'provider|base_url|api_key' ui/src/` returns no new components/routes for provider config. Covers CON-008, FR-009.

AC-021: Given the implementation, when the model field is inspected in the config schema, then `model` is a plain string with no model-listing/validation code path calling a provider API.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: no HTTP client call to a provider `/models` endpoint exists in the diff. Covers CON-009, FR-009.

AC-022: Given the implementation, when the dispatch path is inspected, then Dev Team still invokes `opencode run` and does not add a direct Dev Team ‚Üí LLM HTTP client.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: dispatch path still calls `opencode run`; no new LLM HTTP client struct in `internal/role/` or `internal/pipeline/`. Covers CON-007, FR-010.
