## Summary

**Feature**: multiple-llm-providers ‚Äî make the LLM provider/model backing each Dev Team role configurable.

**Workspace**: Brownfield. Go backend + React UI. Currently `opencode run` is dispatched with no `-m` flag (global opencode default used for all roles). Change threads a resolved `provider/model` + provider API-key env var into the existing tmux/direct dispatcher.

**Artifacts submitted** (spec, acceptance, repos) via `devteam artifact submit`. Note + `pass` signal recorded.

**Key decisions (from human answers ‚Üí constraint register CON-001..CON-010):**
- `providers:` section in `devteam.yaml`; per-role `model` in `provider/model` form; optional top-level default.
- API keys from env vars named in `api_key_env` ‚Äî never in config files (security).
- Fail fast + surface on provider unavailability/auth error ‚Äî no silent fallback (resiliency).
- No UI changes, no model catalog ‚Äî operator types free-form model ID (scope).
- No `providers:` section = today's behavior, byte-for-byte (non-regression, CON-009).

**Gate**: No constitution present (N/A). All 9 gate criteria met ‚Äî user stories prioritized P1/P1/P2/P3, each independently testable; FR-001..010 enumerated; SC-001..006 measurable; assumptions tagged; 10 traceable constraints; 18 acceptance criteria (Given/When/Then + test level + verification), covering happy paths, error/empty/edge cases, and non-regression.

Skipped: no `questions.json` round 2 ‚Äî the 8 human answers covered all ambiguity; one opencode base_url mechanism detail left as a flagged `[ASSUMPTION]` for the Architect to confirm during planning (correct handoff per PM role boundaries).
