# Acceptance Criteria ‚Äî Multiple LLM Providers

## US-001: Operator Configures a Provider

AC-001: Given `devteam.yaml` with `providers.anthropic: { base_url: "...", api_key_env: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }` and `roles.developer.model: "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4"`, when the pipeline dispatches the developer role, then the assembled `opencode run` command contains `-m anthropic/claude-sonnet-4` and the agent process environment contains `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<value>`
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert the constructed tmux `agentCmd` (or dispatcher `args`) contains the substring `-m anthropic/claude-sonnet-4`; assert the env var name appears in the `-e` pairs passed to tmux (or in `cmd.Env` for the direct path)

AC-002: Given `devteam.yaml` declaring two providers `anthropic` and `openai` with distinct `base_url` and `api_key_env`, and `roles.developer.model: "anthropic/x"` and `roles.tester.model: "openai/y"`, when both roles are dispatched, then the developer command uses `-m anthropic/x` with `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in env, and the tester command uses `-m openai/y` with `OPENAI_API_KEY` in env
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Dispatch both roles from the same config, assert each constructed command carries its own `-m` and its own env var

AC-003: Given `devteam.yaml` with a provider entry that omits `base_url` (relying on the opencode provider package default), when a role using that provider is dispatched, then the command carries `-m <provider>/<model>` and the provider's `api_key_env` is present
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert `-m` substring and env var name present; assert no failure from the missing `base_url` at config load

AC-004: Given `devteam.yaml` with a role that has no `model` field and no top-level default `model`, when that role is dispatched, then the constructed `opencode run` command does NOT contain the `-m` flag (byte-for-byte identical to today's command)
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert the command string/args do not contain `-m`

## US-002: Provider Auth Failure Surfaces to Operator

AC-005: Given a role configured with `model: "anthropic/x"` where `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is unset or empty in the dispatcher's environment, when the role is dispatched, then the dispatch fails fast (opencode is not invoked, or is invoked and fails) and `DispatchResult.Success=false` with an `Error` string naming the missing `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Unset the env var in the test process, dispatch the role, assert `Success==false` and `Error` contains `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`

AC-006: Given a role configured with a provider whose base URL is unreachable (connection refused), when the role is dispatched, then `DispatchResult.Success=false` and `DispatchResult.Error` includes the provider/model and a short excerpt of the captured opencode output
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Point a provider base URL at a refused port (or unset key so opencode errors immediately), dispatch, assert `Success==false` and `Error` is non-empty and references the failure

AC-007: Given a dispatch that failed due to a provider error, when the pipeline evaluates the phase gate, then the gate is NOT marked passed
  Test level: integration
  Verification: Run a phase dispatch that fails via AC-005/AC-006, assert the resulting `PhaseStatus` is not `StatusPassed` and the feature does not advance to the next phase

## US-003: Configuration Validation at Load Time

AC-008: Given `devteam.yaml` with `roles.developer.model: "claude-sonnet-4"` (no `provider/` prefix), when `LoadConfig` runs, then it returns an error whose message indicates the model must be in `provider/model` form
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Call `LoadConfig` with the malformed yaml, assert error is non-nil and contains "provider/model"

AC-009: Given `devteam.yaml` with `roles.developer.model: "anthropic/x"` but no `providers.anthropic` entry, when `LoadConfig` runs, then it returns an error naming the unknown provider `anthropic`
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Call `LoadConfig`, assert error non-nil and contains "anthropic"

AC-010: Given `devteam.yaml` with a provider entry whose `api_key_env` is empty, when `LoadConfig` runs, then it returns an error requiring a non-empty env var name
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Call `LoadConfig`, assert error non-nil and message references `api_key_env`

AC-011: Given `devteam.yaml` with two provider entries using the same name, when `LoadConfig` runs, then it returns an error about the duplicate provider name
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert error non-nil and message references the duplicate

AC-012: Given `devteam.yaml` with a valid `providers:` section and valid per-role `model` fields, when `LoadConfig` runs, then it returns no error and the parsed `Config` exposes the providers and models
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert `cfg.Providers` and the resolved per-role models match the yaml

## US-004: Default Provider/Model Override

AC-013: Given `devteam.yaml` with a top-level `model: "ollama/glm-5.2:cloud"` and no `roles.pm.model`, when the PM role is dispatched, then the command carries `-m ollama/glm-5.2:cloud`
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert the constructed command contains `-m ollama/glm-5.2:cloud`

AC-014: Given `devteam.yaml` with a top-level `model` AND `roles.developer.model: "anthropic/x"`, when the developer role is dispatched, then the command carries `-m anthropic/x` (per-role wins over top-level default)
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert the constructed command contains `-m anthropic/x` and NOT the top-level default model string

## Non-Regression (CON-009 / FR-009)

AC-015: Given `devteam.yaml` with no `providers:` section and no `model` fields anywhere, when any role is dispatched, then the `opencode run` command is byte-for-byte identical to the command constructed before this feature (no `-m` flag, no new env vars)
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Construct the dispatch command for a role under the old config and under the empty new config, assert equality

AC-016: Given `devteam.yaml` with no `providers:` section and no `model` fields, when `LoadConfig` runs, then it returns no error (existing deployments keep loading)
  Test level: unit
  Verification: Assert `LoadConfig` error is nil and `Config.Providers` is empty/nil

## Edge Cases (CON/FR)

AC-017: Given `roles.developer.model: "openai/gpt-4o-2024/o8"` (model id contains a slash), when `LoadConfig` runs, then it parses `provider=openai`, `model=gpt-4o-2024/o8` without error
  Test level: unit
