+| VI. Cross-Repo Coherence | Compliant | Single repo (devteam) in scope; no cross-repo coordination required for this feature. |
+| VII. Self-Bootstrap | Compliant | Feature improves the platform's own dispatch mechanism, processed through the platform's pipeline. |
+| VIII. Go, Minimal Dependencies | Compliant | No new runtime dependency; config parsing extends existing Go `internal/config`; `opencode run -m` is the existing CLI surface. |
+| IX. Pipeline Governance | Compliant | Inception rules followed; PM wrote acceptance criteria with test levels; overconfidence-prevention checks applied (empty states, error paths covered in edge cases). |
+| X. Learn From Cistern | Compliant | Structured config (not freeform); role identity preserved; phase gates remain mechanically enforced. |
