# Feature Specification: Multiple LLM Providers

**Feature Branch**: `multiple-llm-providers`

**Created**: 2026-06-26

**Status**: Draft

**Input**: Human answers (inception Q&A) ‚Äî make LLM provider/model configurable per-role, server-side config in `devteam.yaml`, credentials via env vars, fail-fast on provider errors.

## Workspace Summary (Brownfield)

This feature modifies the **Dev Team platform** itself ‚Äî a Go backend (`cmd/`, `internal/`) with a React/TypeScript frontend (`ui/`).

- **Language/Build**: Go (`go build ./cmd/devteam/`), Node (`ui/`, npm).
- **Config**: `devteam.yaml` at repo root, parsed by `internal/config/config.go` (`Config` struct, YAML tags). `validateConfig` enforces 6 phases and 6 roles.
- **Agent dispatch**: `internal/role/dispatcher.go` and `internal/role/tmux.go` invoke `opencode run --dangerously-skip-permissions --agent <role>` with `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` pointing at a temp context dir, `OPENCODE_DISABLE_PROJECT_CONFIG=1`.
- **Current provider/model selection**: None in `devteam.yaml`. The model is fixed by the operator's global `opencode.json` (`~/.config/opencode/opencode.json`) and/or the repo's `opencode.json` (which currently only sets plugins/instructions, no provider block). The dispatched agent inherits whatever provider/model the opencode installation resolves ‚Äî Dev Team has no per-role/per-phase control.
- **Conventions**: YAML config with snake_case keys; `Config` struct with `yaml:"..."` tags; `LoadConfig` + `validateConfig` pattern; Go tests in `*_test.go` using `httptest` and temp dirs.

---
# Acceptance Criteria ‚Äî multiple-llm-providers

Each criterion maps to a user story and constraint. Test level and verification method are explicit.

## US-1 / US-2 ‚Äî Per-role provider selection + provider registry

- AC-001: Given `devteam.yaml` with no `providers:` section, when `LoadConfig` is called, then it succeeds and `Config.Providers` is empty (backward-compatible).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config_test.go` ‚Äî `LoadConfig` on a minimal `devteam.yaml` returns no error and empty `Providers`.

- AC-002: Given `devteam.yaml` with a `providers:` section declaring `ollama` (`base_url: http://localhost:11434/v1`), when `LoadConfig` is called, then `Config.Providers["ollama"].BaseURL == "http://localhost:11434/v1"`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config_test.go` ‚Äî assert parsed `Providers` map contains the declared base URL.

- AC-003: Given `devteam.yaml` where role `pm` has `provider: ollama` and `model: glm-5.2:cloud`, when `LoadConfig` is called, then `Config.Roles["pm"]` carries `provider=ollama` and `model=glm-5.2:cloud`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: `config_test.go` ‚Äî assert per-role provider/model fields parsed.

- AC-004: Given `devteam.yaml` where role `pm` references `provider: nonexistent`, when `LoadConfig` is called, then it returns an error naming the missing provider (`nonexistent`).
  Test level: unit
---
repos:
  - name: devteam
    path: .
    role: primary
    changes: >
      Add `providers:` section and per-role `provider`/`model` fields to
      `devteam.yaml` schema (`internal/config/config.go` + tests). Extend
      `internal/role/dispatcher.go` and `internal/role/tmux.go` to inject
      an `opencode.json` declaring the configured provider/model into the
      per-dispatch `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` context dir. Pass through operator
      credential env vars; fail fast on missing creds, unreachable base URLs,
      and auth errors. UI unchanged (no provider/model display).
