## Assumptions

- [ASSUMPTION: config is read fresh per dispatch, not cached for the pipeline run.] Allows operator to change `devteam.yaml` between phases; matches the existing per-dispatch temp-dir pattern. (FR-013)
- [ASSUMPTION: the `provider` and `model` fields in `devteam.yaml` map to opencode's `<provider>/<model>` model syntax (e.g., `ollama/glm-5.2:cloud`).] The generated `config.json` writes this combined form into the `model` field. If opencode uses a different schema (separate `provider` + `model` keys), the Architect resolves the exact mapping during planning.
- [ASSUMPTION: opencode reads `config.json` from `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` with higher precedence than `~/.config/opencode/config.json`.] This is the documented opencode behavior and is what makes per-role override work without mutating the operator's global config. (CON-011)
- [ASSUMPTION: Dev Team forwards all `*_API_KEY` env vars present in the operator environment into the agent process, plus any explicitly named in the provider entry (`env: [ANTHROPIC_API_KEY]` optional field).] This avoids a hardcoded provider‚Üíenv-var map (which would need updating for every new provider) while keeping `devteam.yaml` free of secrets. The Architect picks the exact forwarding mechanism during planning. The conservative default (forward all `*_API_KEY` present) means an unset key is simply absent from the agent env ‚Äî no placeholder injected ‚Äî so the provider's own auth error surfaces via US-004.
- [ASSUMPTION: the existing `OPENCODE_DISABLE_PROJECT_CONFIG=1` env var set in the dispatcher does not suppress `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` `config.json` loading.] `OPENCODE_DISABLE_PROJECT_CONFIG` disables project-local `.opencode/` config, not the `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` temp config. If it does suppress temp config, the Architect must use a different override mechanism (e.g., a `--model` CLI flag on `opencode run`).

