# Acceptance Criteria ‚Äî Multiple LLM Providers

Every criterion is testable at a specific level with a concrete verification. Traceability to user stories (US-NNN) and constraints (CON-NNN) in parentheses where relevant.

## US-001 ‚Äî Operator configures a provider per role

AC-001: Given a `devteam.yaml` with a `providers:` section mapping `pm` to `{provider: ollama, model: glm-5.2:cloud}` and `developer` to `{provider: openai, model: gpt-4o, base_url: https://api.openai.com/v1}`, when the pipeline dispatches the PM, then the temp `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` for that dispatch contains a `config.json` whose `model` field resolves to `ollama/glm-5.2:cloud`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert the generated `config.json` bytes contain `"model":"ollama/glm-5.2:cloud"` (or equivalent opencode-recognized form). (CON-001, CON-002, CON-004, CON-011)

AC-002: Given the same config, when the pipeline dispatches the developer, then that dispatch's `config.json` `model` resolves to `openai/gpt-4o` and includes the `base_url` override targeting `https://api.openai.com/v1`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert generated `config.json` contains the openai model string and the base_url override. (CON-003, CON-011)

AC-003: Given a `devteam.yaml` with no `providers:` section, when the pipeline dispatches any role, then the temp `OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` does NOT contain a `config.json` with a `model` field (or contains none that overrides the global), so opencode falls back to `~/.config/opencode/config.json`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert no model-override `config.json` is written when the role is unmapped. (CON-001, SC-003)

AC-004: Given a `providers:` section that maps only `pm` (omits `developer`), when the developer is dispatched, then the developer falls back to the global default ‚Äî no `config.json` model override written.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert developer dispatch produces no model override. (edge: partial mapping)

AC-005: Given `providers:` maps `pm` to `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5`, when the PM agent is dispatched, then the generated `config.json` `model` field is `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5` (or opencode-equivalent).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert `config.json` bytes contain the anthropic model string. (CON-001, CON-002)

## US-002 ‚Äî Credentials from the environment

AC-006: Given `providers:` maps `developer` to `openai/gpt-4o` and `OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-test-123` is set in the operator shell, when the developer agent is dispatched via the tmux path, then the agent process environment contains `OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-test-123`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: in a tmux dispatch test, capture the agent process env (via a wrapper that prints env) and assert `OPENAI_API_KEY` is present with the operator's value. (CON-005, CON-009)

AC-007: Given the same config but `OPENAI_API_KEY` is unset in the operator shell, when the developer agent is dispatched via tmux, then the agent process environment does NOT contain `OPENAI_API_KEY` and the dispatch result surfaces the resulting provider auth failure (no placeholder credential is injected).
  Test level: integration
  Verification: assert `OPENAI_API_KEY` absent from agent env AND dispatch result `Error` is non-empty naming the credential/provider failure. (CON-005, CON-006, CON-009)

AC-008: Given the direct (non-tmux) dispatch path is used, when `developer` is mapped to a provider requiring `OPENAI_API_KEY` and that var is set, then `cmd.Env` for the opencode process includes `OPENAI_API_KEY`.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert `cmd.Env` (or the constructed env slice) contains `OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-test-123`. (CON-005, CON-010)

AC-009: Given any `devteam.yaml` with provider entries, when the repo is scanned, then no API key value appears in `devteam.yaml` or any committed file.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert `devteam.yaml` example/test fixtures contain no `sk-`, no `*_API_KEY:` with a value, only field names. (CON-005, SC-005)

## US-003 ‚Äî OpenAI-compatible endpoints via base URL override

AC-010: Given `providers:` maps `reviewer` to `{provider: openai-compatible, model: local-llm, base_url: http://localhost:11434/v1}`, when the reviewer agent is dispatched, then the generated `config.json` causes opencode to target `http://localhost:11434/v1` rather than `https://api.openai.com/v1`.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: dispatch reviewer with a local mock OpenAI-compatible server on :11434; assert the mock receives the request (the real api.openai.com does not). (CON-003, SC-002)

AC-011: Given a provider entry with no `base_url`, when the agent is dispatched, then the generated `config.json` does not set a base URL override and opencode uses its built-in default endpoint for that provider.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert `config.json` has no base_url key (or an empty one) for the entry; confirm opencode default is unchanged. (edge: no base_url)

## US-004 ‚Äî Fail fast on provider unavailability

AC-012: Given a provider entry with `base_url: http://127.0.0.1:9/no-such-server`, when the role is dispatched, then the dispatch result is marked failed (`Success=false`) with `Error` containing the provider failure (connection refused or equivalent), not a generic "session ended immediately".
  Test level: integration
  Verification: dispatch with bogus base_url; assert `result.Success == false` and `result.Error` matches /connection refused|unreachable|provider/i. (CON-006, SC-004)

AC-013: Given a provider entry whose required credential env var is unset, when the role is dispatched, then the dispatch fails fast (no hang beyond the existing stale-session timeout) and the operator-visible error names the missing credential as the likely cause.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: assert failure occurs within stale-session window and `result.Error` mentions the missing credential. (CON-006, CON-009)

AC-014: Given a provider that returns 401/403 mid-pipeline, when the role is dispatched, then the pipeline does NOT retry and does NOT fall back to another provider; the single failed dispatch result is surfaced.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: assert exactly one dispatch attempt for the role (no retry counter incremented), and no alternate provider's `config.json` is generated for that role. (CON-006, FR-010)

## US-005 ‚Äî Free-form model id, no catalog validation

AC-015: Given a provider entry with `model: this-model-does-not-exist-12345`, when Dev Team loads `devteam.yaml`, then no network call to a model-catalog endpoint (e.g. `/v1/models`) is made and no model-id validation runs.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: instrument HTTP in the config-load path; assert zero catalog requests. Code audit: no `models` list/validate function. (CON-008, FR-011)

AC-016: Given an invalid model id, when the role is dispatched, then the provider (not Dev Team) surfaces the rejection via the US-004 fail-fast path.
  Test level: integration
  Verification: dispatch with invalid model; assert `result.Error` comes from the provider response, not from a Dev Team pre-validation step. (CON-008)

## UI scope (operator-only)

AC-017: Given the web UI is loaded for any feature and phase, when an operator views any role or phase screen, then no provider name or model id is rendered anywhere in the UI.
  Test level: e2e
  Verification: Playwright e2e ‚Äî load the feature dashboard, assert no element text matches /provider|model|anthropic|openai|ollama|base_url/i on any role/phase view. (CON-007, FR-012, SC-006)

## Config-schema / regression

AC-018: Given a `devteam.yaml` containing the existing sections (`database`, `pipeline`, `roles`, `extensions`, `plugins`, `intake`, `spec_repo`) AND a new `providers:` section, when the binary loads config, then all existing sections still parse and the new `providers:` section parses without breaking the others.
  Test level: unit
  Verification: load the combined config, assert each existing section's fields are populated AND `providers` is populated. (CON-012)

AC-019: Given an empty `providers:` section (`providers: {}` or `providers:` with no entries), when the binary loads config, then load succeeds and every role falls back to the global default (AC-003 behavior).
  Test level: unit
  Verification: assert config load returns an empty/nil providers map with no error. (edge: empty providers)

AC-020: Given a `providers:` entry with an unknown provider name and no `base_url`, when the role is dispatched, then opencode rejects it at launch and the failure is surfaced via the US-004 path (Dev Team does not pre-validate the provider name).
  Test level: integration
  Verification: dispatch with bogus provider name; assert `result.Success == false` and Dev Team did not perform a pre-launch provider-name check. (edge: unknown provider)
