# Dev Team CLI

The Dev Team platform is a multi-agent pipeline orchestrator at `github.com/MichielDean/devteam`. It runs features through a fixed 6-phase AIDLC pipeline using agent dispatch (opencode).

## Architecture

- **Binary**: `~/go/bin/devteam`
- **Repo**: `~/source/devteam` (personal repo, direct push to main)
- **Web UI**: Running as systemd service on `:8765` (service: `devteam-web.service`)
- **Config**: `devteam.yaml` in project root
- **State**: `.devteam-state.yaml` per feature in `specs/NNN-<slug>/`
- **Spec Worktrees**: Each feature gets its own git worktree at `~/worktrees/devteam-specs/<feature-id>/` on branch `spec/<feature-id>`, branched from `origin/main`. All agents run with CWD = the worktree. Artifacts are committed to the `spec/<feature-id>` branch after each gate passes.
- **Phases**: inception ‚Üí planning ‚Üí construction ‚Üí review ‚Üí testing ‚Üí delivery
- **Roles**: pm, architect, developer, reviewer, tester, ops

### CRITICAL: Platform, Not Project

The Dev Team is a **platform** that works across any repository ‚Äî Go, Node, Python, Rust, etc. Phase instructions, gate checks, and role instructions must NEVER reference:
- Specific build commands (go build, npm run build, cargo build)
- Specific test commands (go test, npm test, npx playwright test)
- Specific file names (go.mod, package.json, playwright.config.ts)
- Specific ports (8765, 18765)
- Repository-specific helper scripts (run-tests.sh)
- Language-specific patterns (json tags, omitempty, httptest)

Instead, instructions should tell agents to **discover** the project's build/test infrastructure and use whatever commands the project supports. The gate evaluator already discovers test commands by checking for go.mod, package.json, etc. ‚Äî it doesn't hardcode them.

## Commands

### CLI Mode (default)

```bash
# Check pipeline status
devteam status

# Create a feature from a loose idea
devteam intake --type loose --text "Your feature idea" --priority 1

# Create a feature from an external spec
devteam intake --type external --file path/to/spec.md --title "Feature Title" --priority 2

# Run the current phase of a feature (dispatches agent)
devteam run <feature-id>

# Run the full autonomous pipeline (run ‚Üí gate ‚Üí advance/recirculate loop)
---
